The application lacks in many areas.  While most of the food is standard recipes mostly from bloggers and commercial sites, the system has hundreds of flaws, most importantly it's lack of support, FAQ,s TOS, and Community Guidelines.  The answer to every question is to send an email, which sometimes get's answered and sometimes does not.  The forums are the same old same old on a daily basis as the there are very few new users that actually interact.  The site is competition based, where any user can take cover photos for your recipes, therefore being a competition there should be rules and TOS for uploading photos, but there are none.  Instead the recipes are flooded with Google photos mostly used to steal covers, or in other words unfair competition.  The other missing element to this application is proper moderation of forums.  Many threads are removed for "unknown reasons" especially when they involve matters that are application issues, as well as abusive attacks, trolls, etc. therefore I DO NOT recommend this application as there are many other stronger, well run, cleaner & all around more solid apps.  ATC has potential, but currently fails in it's current state.
